gentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly crosses real external boundaries: source APIs plus actual email transport/inbox delivery (REAL-INFRA yes). In-process mocks can pass while masking SMTP/API auth, TLS, routing, or inbox acceptance failures (MOCK-HIDE yes). Not Agentic by minimum boundary: assertion is end-to-end delivery to recipient inbox; model output quality is not the correctness target, so summary generation can be deterministic/stubbed for this test. MULTI-STEP agent pipeline is not required by behavior text.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled job in an environment with reachable test instances of the three data endpoints and a real email delivery path to a test mailbox. Verify the mailbox receives one message for configured recipients, with expected subject/report attachment/body presence and traceable run timestamp.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary failure boundary is orchestration/persistence across components: delivery failure handling -> local persistence -> subsequent-run retry state pickup (MOCK-MISS yes). Integration with real local filesystem is enough to catch missing write/read/state bugs. REAL-INFRA check: no mandatory real network needed; unreachable email can be simulated by adapter error. System is not strictly required unless validating true scheduler/transport behavior. LLM-DEP no, MULTI-STEP no. Rejected System: behavior text does not require real SMTP/network stack; it requires retry